# Write your MySQL query statement below
SELECT DISTINCT l1.num AS ConsecutiveNums
FROM Logs l1
JOIN Logs l2 ON l1.id = l2.id - 1
JOIN Logs l3 ON l1.id = l3.id - 2
WHERE l1.num = l2.num
  AND l2.num = l3.num;

We need to find if the consecutive num are same or not so we do a self join and check the previous 2 values and compare with the current value to see if the current value matches
the previous 2 values or not.
